{"type": "root", "attrs": {"type": "node", "context": "vop", "internal": "displacenml", "icon": "VOP/displacenml", "version": null, "namespace": null}, "body": [{"level": 0, "type": "title", "indent": 0, "text": ["Displace Along Normal"], "extent": [73, 99]}, {"type": "summary", "indent": 0, "text": ["Displaces the surface along the surface normal by a given amount."], "extent": [99, 173]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": ["This operator displaces the surface along the surface normal by a given\namount. The displacement is anti-aliased."], "extent": [173, 288]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": ["You will often pipe the output of a pattern operator such as Stripes,\nBoxes, or Rings into the ", {"type": "q", "text": ["amount"]}, " input. You can further control the\namount of displacement by the ", {"type": "q", "text": ["scale"]}, " multiplier."], "extent": [288, 478]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": ["Typically, this operator will be used in a displacement shader, with\nboth outputs piped into the corresponding inputs of the ", {"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/vop/output", "type": "link", "text": ["Output Variables"], "fullpath": "/nodes/vop/output"}, " operator.\nAlternatively, it can be appear in a surface shader, in which case the\ndisplaced normal would be normalized and then connected to the ", {"type": "code", "text": ["nN"]}, "\ninput of the ", {"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/vop/lighting", "type": "link", "text": ["Lighting Model"], "fullpath": "/nodes/vop/lighting"}, " operator."], "extent": [478, 846]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": ["The input normal (", {"type": "code", "text": ["nN"]}, ") should be normalized if explicitly connected. If\nthe position (", {"type": "code", "text": ["P"]}, ") and normal (", {"type": "code", "text": ["nN"]}, ") inputs are not connected, the global\nvariables by the same names will be used instead."], "extent": [846, 1044]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": ["Normals are automatically recomputed and set for output."], "extent": [1044, 1102]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": ["Note that in the SOP/POP contexts, the shears and object space\ndeformation are not implemented. They exist as parameters for\ncompleteness only."], "extent": [1102, 1247]}, {"type": "tip_group", "body": [{"type": "tip", "indent": 0, "role": "item", "extent": [1247, 1252], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["When doing a displacement in RenderMan, be sure to add an\n    ", {"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/vop/rsl_transform", "type": "link", "text": ["RSL Transform"], "fullpath": "/nodes/vop/rsl_transform"}, " node to P before piping it\n    into your noise VOP. Make this ", {"type": "q", "text": ["current to world"]}, " and change the\n    displace space at object level to be the camera you are rendering\n    through. Otherwise the noise will slide."], "extent": [1252, 1573]}], "container": true}], "container": true, "role": "item_group"}, {"level": 1, "id": "parameters", "container": true, "type": "parameters_section", "indent": 0, "role": "section", "extent": [1573, 1585], "body": [{"type": "parameters_item_group", "body": [{"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Displacement Amount"], "extent": [1585, 1607], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 8, "text": ["Overall displacement amount, including the amount for shears."], "extent": [1607, 1687]}], "container": true, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Scale"], "extent": [1687, 1694], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 8, "text": ["A multiplier of the amount in the perpendicular direction."], "extent": [1694, 1771]}], "container": true, "role": "item"}], "container": true, "role": "item_group"}], "text": "Parameters"}, {"level": 1, "id": "related", "container": true, "type": "related_section", "indent": 0, "role": "section", "extent": [1771, 1780], "body": [{"type": "bullet_group", "body": [{"blevel": 2, "type": "bullet", "indent": 0, "text": [{"scheme": null, "value": "/shade/normalmaps", "type": "link", "text": "", "fullpath": "/shade/normalmaps"}], "extent": [1780, 1803]}, {"blevel": 2, "type": "bullet", "indent": 0, "text": [{"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/vop/displace", "type": "link", "text": "", "fullpath": "/nodes/vop/displace"}], "extent": [1803, 1825]}, {"blevel": 2, "type": "bullet", "indent": 0, "text": [{"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/vop/displacetexture", "type": "link", "text": "", "fullpath": "/nodes/vop/displacetexture"}], "extent": [1825, 1854]}, {"blevel": 2, "type": "bullet", "indent": 0, "text": [{"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/vop/boxes", "type": "link", "text": "", "fullpath": "/nodes/vop/boxes"}], "extent": [1854, 1873]}, {"blevel": 2, "type": "bullet", "indent": 0, "text": [{"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/vop/cavities", "type": "link", "text": "", "fullpath": "/nodes/vop/cavities"}], "extent": [1873, 1895]}, {"blevel": 2, "type": "bullet", "indent": 0, "text": [{"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/vop/cellcracks", "type": "link", "text": "", "fullpath": "/nodes/vop/cellcracks"}], "extent": [1895, 1919]}, {"blevel": 2, "type": "bullet", "indent": 0, "text": [{"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/vop/lighting", "type": "link", "text": "", "fullpath": "/nodes/vop/lighting"}], "extent": [1919, 1941]}, {"blevel": 2, "type": "bullet", "indent": 0, "text": [{"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/vop/scales", "type": "link", "text": "", "fullpath": "/nodes/vop/scales"}], "extent": [1941, 1962]}], "container": true}], "text": "Related"}], "title": ["Displace Along Normal"], "summary": ["Displaces the surface along the surface normal by a given amount."]}